JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Diamond miner De Beers&rsquo; fourth cycle of rough diamond sales for this year has generated $520-million. This was slightly lower than the $586-million achieved in the third sales cycle. De Beers CEO Bruce Cleaver said the company continued to see steady demand for rough diamonds, despite the industry entering a typically quieter season. &ldquo;Sentiment remains positive as we head towards the important Las Vegas trade show in early June.&rdquo;